## 🏗️ Mode-by-Mode Prompt Templates

### 🎨 Restyle (Product Finish & Mood)

> *Restyle this scene using a \[material style] approach. Incorporate \[materials or textures] with \[lighting style] for a \[mood or aesthetic]. The result should evoke \[emotion or use-case].*

**Example:**

> “Restyle using a tech-forward CMF: brushed steel, matte black polymer, and cool ambient lighting. Make it feel engineered and modern.”

---

### 🌌 Imagine (Visual Moodboards & Concept Art)

> *Imagine a \[setting] filled with \[key visual features]. Use \[lighting style] to create a \[vibe or emotion] atmosphere. This supports ideas for \[industry or concept].*

**Example:**

> “Imagine a minimalist, all-white meditation chamber with floating panels and soft ambient shadows. It should feel weightless and introspective — ideal for wellness tech concepts.”

---

### 🏙️ Background (Scene Context Behind Product)

> *Create a background of a \[setting type] with a \[ground material] and \[lighting condition]. The scene should feel \[mood or style] and support visuals for \[product or use-case].*

**Example:**

> “Background of a modern workshop with concrete bench, copper circuitry, and neutral daylight. Aimed at showcasing premium PC components.”

---

Modular Prompt Starters
Let users build their own prompts using mix-and-match slots like Mad Libs:

Template A — Restyle:

“Restyle this scene using [primary materials] and [surface finish]. Illuminate with [lighting type] for a [mood/emotion] feel — suitable for [season/brand/style].”

Template B — Background:

“Background of a [setting type] with [floor or surface type] and [light quality]. It should feel [emotional tone] and support [product type or audience].”

Template C — Imagine:

“Imagine a [thematic world or space] with [core visual features] and [light behavior]. The mood is [emotion or tone], designed to explore [industry or vision].”


